  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch3\u003eQuick Links\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#skip-tpm-and-secure-check-using-command-prompt\"\u003eSkip TPM and Secure Check Using Command Prompt\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#bypass-secure-boot-and-tpm-check-using-rufus\"\u003eBypass Secure Boot and TPM Check Using Rufus\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#install-future-windows-11-updates-by-modifying-the-iso-file\"\u003eInstall Future Windows 11 Updates by Modifying the ISO File\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e\u003cul\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"#what-happens-if-you-install-windows-11-on-unsupported-hardware\"\u003eWhat Happens if You Install Windows 11 on Unsupported Hardware?\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e \u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_0\"\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eKey Takeaways\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e \n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e You can bypass the TPM and Secure Boot requirements for installing Windows 11 with a simple command or using tools like Rufus. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e Installing Windows 11 on ineligible hardware can lead to compatibility issues and prevent future security and feature updates. \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e You\u0026#39;ll need to install future Windows 11 updates manually using ISO images of newer versions. \u003c/li\u003e\n \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eOfficially, you can\u0026#39;t install Windows 11 on ineligible hardware because of Secure Boot and TPM hardware requirements. However, there are two easy workarounds that allow you to upgrade your old Windows 10 PC to Windows 11. I\u0026#39;ll share them below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"skip-tpm-and-secure-check-using-command-prompt\"\u003e 1. Skip TPM and Secure Check Using Command Prompt \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can upgrade your non-compatible Windows 10 PC to Windows 11 using a simple command-line hack. Before you start, \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/ultimate-windows-10-data-backup-guide/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eback up your Windows computer\u003c/a\u003e so that you can revert the changes if something goes wrong.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo get started, \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/windows-11-download-iso/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003edownload the latest version of the Windows 11 ISO\u003c/a\u003e onto your computer. I recommend using the \u003cstrong\u003eMedia Creation Tool\u003c/strong\u003e to download the ISO, as it will automatically detect the correct language preference to match your existing installation. If there\u0026#39;s a mismatch, the upgrade option will be greyed out. Once the ISO is ready, right-click the \u003cstrong\u003eISO\u003c/strong\u003e file and choose \u003cstrong\u003eMount\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1148\" height=\"296\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"File Explorer context menu showing Mount option when right-clicked on an ISO Image\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThen, open \u003cstrong\u003eFile Explorer\u003c/strong\u003e, locate the mounted drive in the left pane, and note the drive letter assigned to it. If you double-click the mounted drive, you can see its content, including the \u003cstrong\u003esetup.exe\u003c/strong\u003e file.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1280\" height=\"558\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"contents of an extracted Windows 11 ISO Image in File Explorer\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFinally, click \u003cstrong\u003eStart\u003c/strong\u003e, type \u003cstrong\u003ecmd\u003c/strong\u003e, and click \u003cstrong\u003eCommand Prompt\u003c/strong\u003e from the results. In the Command Prompt window, type the following command:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eG:\\setup /product server\u003c/code\u003e \u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReplace \u003cstrong\u003eG:\\\u003c/strong\u003e with the drive letter assigned to your mounted drive and hit \u003cstrong\u003eEnter\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"799\" height=\"153\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Command Prompt with the setup product server command \" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/command-prompt-install-windows.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e When the warning dialog appears, click \u003cstrong\u003eRun\u003c/strong\u003e, then click \u003cstrong\u003eYes\u003c/strong\u003e. This will launch the \u003cstrong\u003eWindows Server Setup\u003c/strong\u003e, which is perfectly normal.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the next screen, click \u003cstrong\u003eChange how the setup downloads updates\u003c/strong\u003e and choose \u003cstrong\u003eNot right now\u003c/strong\u003e. Under \u003cstrong\u003eChoose What to Keep\u003c/strong\u003e, select \u003cstrong\u003eKeep files, settings, and apps\u003c/strong\u003e to install Windows 11 without deleting your apps. If not, click \u003cstrong\u003eNothing\u003c/strong\u003e. Then, click \u003cstrong\u003eNext\u003c/strong\u003e and follow the on-screen instructions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"bypass-secure-boot-and-tpm-check-using-rufus\"\u003e 2. Bypass Secure Boot and TPM Check Using Rufus \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRufus is a popular third-party bootable installation media tool with built-in options to remove \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/how-enable-tpm-secure-boot-before-upgrading-windows-11/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ethe Secure Boot and TPM 2.0 requirements to install Windows 11\u003c/a\u003e. To \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/windows-11-create-bootable-usb-drive/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecreate a bootable USB media\u003c/a\u003e, you need the latest Windows 11 ISO, so keep it handy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eStart by downloading \u003ca href=\"https://rufus.ie/en/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRufus\u003c/a\u003e from the official website. Extract the zip file and double-click to run \u003cstrong\u003eRufus.exe\u003c/strong\u003e. Then, connect the USB drive to your computer and wait for Rufus to detect it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn Rufus, click \u003cstrong\u003eSelect\u003c/strong\u003e, then select the ISO file you downloaded. Leave all the options as default, and then click \u003cstrong\u003eStart\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1284\" height=\"844\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"the Rufus app running on Windows 11\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-rufus-app-running-on-windows-11.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Select the first two options in the \u003cstrong\u003eWindows User Experience\u003c/strong\u003e dialog, as shown in the screenshot below. Feel free to go through the other options to select or unselect them according to your preference.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1089\" height=\"341\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Rufus Windows Installation Customization dialog in Windows 11\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/rufus-windows-installation-customization-dialog-in-windows-11.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eClick \u003cstrong\u003eOK\u003c/strong\u003e and wait for the copying process to complete. Once done, you can use the installation media to \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/how-to-clean-install-windows-11/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eclean install Windows 11\u003c/a\u003e on unsupported hardware.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"install-future-windows-11-updates-by-modifying-the-iso-file\"\u003e Install Future Windows 11 Updates by Modifying the ISO File \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eA major issue with installing Windows 11 on ineligible hardware is that it won\u0026#39;t receive features or security updates. But there\u0026#39;s a workaround.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou can install future updates using the Command Prompt method we discussed above. Make sure to download the ISO image of the Windows 11 version you want to upgrade to, then run the \u003cstrong\u003esetup.exe\u003c/strong\u003e file using the \u003cstrong\u003esetup /product server\u003c/strong\u003e command.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf that doesn\u0026#39;t work, you can modify the contents of the \u003cstrong\u003eappraiserres.dll\u003c/strong\u003e file in the ISO image and then run the setup to perform an upgrade. To get started, download and mount the latest version of Windows 11 ISO.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1148\" height=\"296\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"File Explorer context menu showing Mount option when right-clicked on an ISO Image\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/file-explorer-context-menu-showing-mount-option-when-right-clicked-on-an-iso-image.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Since we can\u0026#39;t directly edit the contents of an ISO image, we first need to copy the files to a new folder. So, double-click to open the mounted drive in File Explorer. You\u0026#39;ll see it in the left pane under \u003cstrong\u003eThis PC\u003c/strong\u003e. Then, press \u003cstrong\u003eCtrl + A\u003c/strong\u003e to select all the files.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eCreate a new folder named \u003cstrong\u003eWindows 11 Update\u003c/strong\u003e and paste the copied content into it. Once done, right-click on the mounted drive and choose \u003cstrong\u003eEject\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1280\" height=\"558\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"contents of an extracted Windows 11 ISO Image in File Explorer\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-contents-of-an-extracted-windows-11-iso-image-in-file-explorer.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Open the \u003cstrong\u003eWindows 11 Updates\u003c/strong\u003e folder, go to the \u003cstrong\u003eSources\u003c/strong\u003e folder, and locate the \u003cstrong\u003eappraiser.dll\u003c/strong\u003e file. Right-click on it and choose \u003cstrong\u003eOpen With \u0026gt; Notepad\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1276\" height=\"418\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"the File Explorer context menu \" data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png\" src=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/screenshot-of-the-file-explorer-context-menu.png\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e In Notepad, press \u003cstrong\u003eCtrl + A\u003c/strong\u003e to select all the contents, press \u003cstrong\u003eBackspace\u003c/strong\u003e to delete it, and then press \u003cstrong\u003eCtrl + S\u003c/strong\u003e to save the file. Now, go back to the Windows 11 Update folder and run the \u003cstrong\u003esetup.exe file\u003c/strong\u003e. Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the upgrade.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"what-happens-if-you-install-windows-11-on-unsupported-hardware\"\u003e What Happens if You Install Windows 11 on Unsupported Hardware? \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhile you can install Windows 11 on your unsupported PC, you still need to know a few things. First, your PC will most likely not receive future updates from Microsoftâ€”including security updates. While a world without Microsoft pushing update notifications every few days might sound like you\u0026#39;re in for a good time, those annoying updates go a long way in keeping your PC safe.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eNote that Microsoft warns of compatibility and stability issues on unsupported hardware. For instance, you\u0026#39;ll likely see a persistent \u0026#34;System requirement not met\u0026#34; message on the desktop or in Settings. However, you can \u003ca href=\"http://www.makeuseof.com/windows-11-remove-system-requirements-not-met-watermark/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eremove this watermark using a registry hack\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSince Microsoft won\u0026#39;t support Windows 10 after October 2025, you may as well just install Windows 11 and continue to install newer updates using these workarounds for as long as possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
